abstracts.cdata!:
The proposed project would consist of:
            (a) the construction of 66 minor irrigation sub-projects
            which will provide irrigation facilities for tracts of land
            ranging from 50 to 700 ha. in size; (b) upland reclamation
            of roughly 4,500 ha involving some 35 sub-projects; (c) the
            development of about 11,000 blocks of fuelwood plantations
            over an area of approximately 127,000 ha.; (d) the
            construction of a total of 850 kms of village roads and 200
            bridges; (e) the construction of simple water supply systems
            for some 2,000 villages; (f) the electrification of about
            300,000 rural households through a program involving some
            2,700 sub-projects; and (g) the improvement of hydrological services.
